\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Can you tell me about the bath arrangements again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Yes, the bath - the bath arrangements was - sometimes you had a bath - in a tin bath in front of the fire in the living room. Other times you had to bath - in the copper. Which was heated - sufficiently to bath in. Later on - there was a neighbour 
come across the yard had three sons - they - had to bath in their copper, and after they'd finished - I was usually pushed across the yard to bath - in the water that was left. So - that's the bathing arrangements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did they ever come and bath in your copper?
