\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 That's right, you'd wear it all the week then you see, 'til the - 'til you went to school like and then you'd put your old }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 school shirt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
 on again you see, it'd be washed on - the school shirt would be washed on Sunday. See, while you was wearing the other one, then it'd be dried in the house if - it - you know to get it dry for Monday morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 It was thought all right to do that amount of washing on a Sunday was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Well it was a question of - had to do. You see, although these foster parents - he was a master tailor, he wasn't in a big business, and the money was scarce. You see, I mean you didn't get - tailoring businesses like you'd get today, such as 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Burtons{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and so on and those kind of people, there was none of that. It was just a shop - and he made perhaps about - two, three suits a week, and that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did many people work for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Only one. And he was a great friend of mine, right through his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 You were never officially adopted were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did your family pay anything towards your keep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No. Only - the only thing they
 paid for after a struggle - was - they used to ask my father for a little bit of money if I wanted new boots or something like that you see, but - they had to catch him in the right mood to get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 In the kitchen. In the living room as you'd call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Were there any other occasions when they ate in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 another room}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No. We had no other room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 The other one wasn't big enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 The other one was a - what they'd call the scullery with the copper and the sink in. Very small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Mostly on the fire in the living room, or a gas stove - a little gas ring - in the - scullery.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh - you'd better stop that. Well in the first place - 
we'll put it like this. Three times a week - I had to get up about - five o'clock, and go down to - the Sneinton markets with a little barrow, I - oh I had a cup of tea then, and probably a slice of bread. Mostly bread and dripping. And then - I had to go
 
to Sneinton market, and fill this barrow up with horse manure because it was all horsedrawn traffic at those days. And push that barrow - right up from Sneinton market, up to Mapperly where he had - a very big garden. And - this would be a matter of - two
 and a half miles, but if not more. Uphill, with this barrow - full of manure. It was emptied into a big water tank he had, and then I had to bring it back, walking both ways - and then I should have breakfast about - eight.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 How old would you have been when you were doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Oh I should say about - eight. And then of course the family had their breakfast about - nine. The - mother and father - father would have breakfast about nine. That's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 But he'd had something first had he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh y
es, he had his - cup of tea with a - a beaten up egg in it, about seven o'clock in the morning. At the - time he got up and washed him. And then of course by nine o'clock, I'd already gone to school, you see, so what happened after that until dinner time 
I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What sort of breakfast did you have, did you have it on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Yes. It'd be sometimes toast and dripping. Bread and dripping. Sometimes a - on a special occasion you'd get a little bit of bread and butter, with jam. But it was mostly shall we say on the frugal side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What did you drink for that meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well just a drink of tea, that's all you got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Was there anything special on Sunday for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh yes. Sundays, it - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 it\rquote  had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132  become more or less like the - the present day Sundays. You'd - get a little bit of - bacon, probably an egg on a Sunday breakfast, and - Sunday dinner - we should have a - a good - dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What sort would it be on the Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 usual}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132  - meat and - two veg or something like that you see, and then - she'd make a boiled - steamed pudding, something of that description. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What would a weekday dinner be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well usually the remains of the Sunday - joint, with - potatoes and vegetables which of course we didn't buy 
many of those because he had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 them from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
 his garden. And - perhaps twice or three times during that week she'd make these - puddings. Suet puddings and so on which was - they're very sustaining, you know, they kept you going. But it - it - it - wasn't a - me
als like you'd have today. They were more shall we say - they - they fed you enough to keep going, but there wasn't - elaborate, we'll put it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What was the next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh you got tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well that - that consisted 
mostly the same thing. Bread and - dripping, bread and margarine or anything you see, you didn't get a lot of butter those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Was that the end of the day or did you have anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh suppertime you - you'd perhaps - you may possibly get a drink of cocoa, it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 depends}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
 - either they - what time you came in, or - you know - there's no fixed rule for supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did you have anything special on Sundays for tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No, not a great deal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Anything special at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No, they didn't make much of Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No, I don't - think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did she bottle fruit or veg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 She didn't bottle it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did she make pickles?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes, she made her own pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Was any beer brewed in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No. There was plenty of wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What special wines did they make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well, she used to make wine from the - some of the fr
uit that we got in the garden. And - dandelion wine and such things like that you see. Ginger wine. Herb beer and so on. Very - elderberry wine, things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 The garden at Mapperley, was it a very big one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes, four gardens in one. Yes. That was on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Haywood Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at Mapperley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 So they grew veg up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh yes, plenty. Plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did they buy any vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh they'd buy them when they're out of season of course, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did they have tinned or dried fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Dried fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No, it'd be bought - it was bought from the - greengrocer. Little bit higher up than where we were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did they keep any livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes, two dogs. One dog 
was mine and one was theirs. My dog was bought - as a birthday present. That came from the kennels - at - Sudbury Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Any hens or pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 How many times a week do you think you ate meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh I should say most days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Tinned meat ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did you ever get extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Not from poaching. We should sometimes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Or those that had been poached?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well probably, we - I don't know, I mean - that didn't concern me as l
ong as it came on the table, that was all that bothered me. But - we did get rabbits because - she used to - get them - probably were poached because at those - that time of day there were a lot of poachers about, and - this father of mine, he - he knew q
uite a lot of them meeting them in the public house you see. And we used to have these rabbits - come in and she used to skin them - 'til eventually her hands got - you know - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 rheumatic}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132  and then I used to skin them. And the skins were used to sell them thos
e days. Take them down to - Tricketts, the - scrap people you know, and we'd sell them - sell them there. They were - the price of a rabbit those days was - you'd get a very very good rabbit for a shilling. Then you'd - skin it, and take the skin back to 
t
he rag man as we called them - and you'd probably get a - penny or tuppence back for the skin. You see. Now today - they - sell you the skin in the weight and then skin it and keep the skin. You see. Oh no, it - it - it wasn't too bad, we had rabbit - I s
hould think once a week at least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did you have fish ever in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes. Yes, she'd get some fish, cook it, that was usually the Friday. Friday meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Do you remember seeing your foster mother having less food so that the rest could have more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Well that's hard to say. Because - she was - shall I say, she was a - very very good woman. And - if it - did come to the occasion like that - she'd do it in such a way that you wouldn't notice it. I wouldn't put it past her. If things were sh
ort - she'd do a thing like that, but I wouldn't actually - she wouldn't let you know about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did your foster father have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 To eat you mean? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Were you allowed to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No, it was a family that - you were - you were taught - t
o share things. That was the main thing. If there's anything as I can be - grateful for today - is the way I was brought up - your character was built in that way that, right from the start you was taught what was right, what was wrong. If you made a mist
a
ke - they used to sit down - they wouldn't - clip your ears or anything like that. I've never known them to hit me. But - they've - sat you down, and they've explained - where you went wrong, and why it was wrong, and consequences of repeatedly doing it w
r
ong. Kind of character building right from the start. From the very beginning, and everything was - shall we say - if things were a bit - tight - you had to share. You see? Now - the foster father - on a Saturday morning - you'd get a ha'penny. Now - you 
didn't have to say - can I have my spending money? If you did you was told - to be patient - and wait, because there were times when he hadn't got so much. And that was how your character was formed, right from the start.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 They sound a marvelous couple.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
They were. They were really - as good as any mother and father - could be. Absolutely, I mean - I knew my own mother and father right through. In constant - visiting them but - these people were every bit as good. Oh yes, they were very very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 They had more influence on you than your real parents I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well, yes, they would. Because I mean - I lived there. You see, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 How much did you go home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well I should go home - perhaps three or four times a week. Just when it s
uited me you see, well when I'd got the time to go you see. Because we were taught as I say - that - money didn't come easy. From a very early age - we were seeping the neighbours yards for a - penny. Tuppence. And you'd have to earn that, and so on you s
ee, there was no - giving you this
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Not unless it was something extraordinary special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Could you choose a bit of what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 You didn't have any choice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What was their attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Well, their attitude was that - if you hadn't got a good appetite you was - either got something on your mind, or - you wasn't feeling too good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Would you have had to have it at the next meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 They were sympathetic about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh yes. Oh no, not - not - no - nothing was put on afterwards. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt coul
d you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh no, you asked for that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way or sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No, only just normal. Just normal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 When everyone else had finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 You waited 'til the very end?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 You had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did they always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 How was the meal served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well usually out of the dishes, there were no fancy dishes on the table or anything like that, I me
an - potatoes and that, they'd be - just - dished out of the pans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Who would do the dishing out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh, the mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Order? Well - me father was - he got his meat shall we say first and then sometimes he'd h
elp himself to vegetables and - sometimes - they'd put it on, but it was mostly him first. And then - me next, and herself last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Where did the nephew come in, or wasn't he always there for meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well he wasn't always there for meals because you see he was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 road sweeper}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
, he got up - he had to be at work - somewhere about four 'til five in the morning, and he had to walk from - Sneinton up to Cannington, that was his depot, then he'd got to come back and the hours in those days were - not these e
ight hour days like it is now. We'd probably see him about teatime. He used to take a little - some sandwiches to - to work, in - the old fashioned - red handkerchief, spotted red handkerchief, you know, used to take them like that. And - he'd have his me
als there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Do you know what roadsweepers were paid in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Not the faintest. All that I know that at Goose Fair time they were called out after the fair, to sweep up, that was when the fair was in the - market place of course, and they did
 usually find - bits of money that had been dropped and so on, of course that was - perks. Of their own. But I couldn't tell you but in any case the - the money wasn't - very great. Couldn't have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Was your real }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 mother an}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132  easy person to talk to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 And your foster mother, was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh yes, very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 I could share them with both her and the father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 And your foster father was easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh yes. Yes. In fact - if you had got any problems - he was the easie
st to talk to, you'd probably mention it to the mother first, and she'd say, well - I think he'd got something on his mind and then he'd - sit - and he'd ask you what it was you see. And - as long as you told him, you'd get the best advice - possible. But
 if he found you out - in a lie or exaggeration then - God help you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Even exaggeration?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Was your real father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No, my God no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well in his own way but I'm afraid it wasn't my way. We didn't get on very well, we'll put it like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 How did your real parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Normally I expect. Normally, they - was - just - went there just the same as you'd visit anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 How did your foster parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Well just like a - an ordinary son would be. You had to behave yourself. Oh yes, you had to behave yourself, there was no - you couldn't talk to them - disrespectful or anything like that. Or no, yes, it was mum - and dad all the time. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did your real parents bring you up to behave towards your sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well I didn't have too much contact with them you see. I mean, I - they were treated as sisters and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 But you wouldn't have seen them very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Not all that much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Were you told to hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Was I told to hit back? Oh yes. Yes. Stand on your own feet. Oh yes. I can always remember my foster par - parent -
 the father - saying to me - you've got two feet my lad. These were his exact words, you've got two feet my lad. Learn to stand on them. That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What kind of person do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh I don't - I - no, I
 don't - I don't think they - they bothered all that much - oh they - I should say - normally good living chap and that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did your foster parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life? You said right from wrong earlier on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Can you enlarge on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Well - you was expected to behave in a proper manner to all people, especially - those older than yourself. You was taught to honour them. And normally you was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid25946\charrsid6829132 taught}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132  to be - shall we call it a good boy. That was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh dear, they abhorred it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No. Unless you was asked. If you was asked a question you answer it. But you were never allowed to join in the ordinary conversation.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 If you did something that was disapproved of you said that your foster parents would talk to you about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did anything else ever happen to you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No. They - they never laid a finger on me
. They could manage it - by talking. I could - I used to sit down, and at times they have made me feel that - bad about it that I've actually cried over it, because I knew I was wrong. And they could manage it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Can you remember any special instance to tell us about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
Oh no. No, no. There weren't many because as I say you was - brought up to know what was right and what was wrong and you didn't make many mistakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What about your real parents, what would happen if you did something they disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 They had no control over me at all, it was left to the foster parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Do you remember any occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No. Except being spoken to of course. And you see thee were plenty of those because everyone makes mistakes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 But not what we call punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh no. No, there was - there was never any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Sent to bed or any of these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Do you think you were unusual in this or not? Do you know what happened to your schoolfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 
I couldn't say. It was none of my business. That was one thing you were taught - from an early age with these people. You just mind your own business. This was another thing, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 You said you received the ideas about how to behave from your foster parents more than your parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Wm.
