\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Yes, I should say the mother did. Because everything was - done - through her. You know, if you wanted to speak to - 
the foster father - you'd usually tell her first - she - it was like the ordinary things are today, children naturally first of all they go to their mums. And that was how it was then, you'd go to your - to her and you'd say, well - what would you do mum?
 And she'd say, well - I'll see what your dad says, and then - when he come down and he'd have a minute to spare he'd say, now what did you want to talk to me about? And then from there it'd go on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did he work very long hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well there was very
 - difficult, I mean he usually start work about eight in the morning - and by working at home there was no - fixed hours, he'd probably work from eight 'til one and then - a little in the afternoon you see. And this workman that he'd got was a very good 
chap. He could practically do the job himself bar the cutting out. And - a lot was left to him. He was a very very reliable sort of chap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 If you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
