\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Did they ever read aloud to you or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 No, but this - nephew did. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 What sort of things did he read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10502885 JF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Well, we had the - now there was a scouting pa
per. He bought that for me each week out of his meager bits of money. And it'd be about a penny I should think or tuppence, I don't know exactly how much it cost but - he'd buy that, I don't - I forget the name of it, it might have been called the Boy Sco
ut or something like that. It was the time Baden Powell was the - found - the leader. And - then other times he'd - he'd sit - and the two of us would - just talk normally, just - and he'd talk to me like in a fatherly way, you see, he'd never been -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7429570 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10426719\charrsid6829132 Was he much older than you?
